# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the ZON website following the official documentation.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version ^2.0.1
- Used npm to install the package (project uses npm as package manager)
- Updated package.json and package-lock.json accordingly

### 2. Code Changes
Modified `app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, placed after the ThemeProvider closing tag
- Followed the official Vercel Analytics Next.js App Router implementation pattern

### 3. Files Modified
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency tree

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Web Analytics quickstart guide for Next.js App Router:
- Fetched latest documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Placed Analytics component at the root layout level for site-wide tracking
- Component is positioned after ThemeProvider to ensure proper rendering
- No additional configuration required - Analytics will automatically track page views

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ TypeScript compilation passed
✅ No new linting errors introduced (existing linting warnings in codebase are unrelated)
✅ Lock files properly updated

## Next Steps

To enable Web Analytics in production:
1. Deploy the changes to Vercel
2. Go to the Vercel dashboard → Analytics tab
3. Click "Enable" to activate Web Analytics
4. Analytics data will start appearing within 24 hours of deployment

## Notes

- The Analytics component is minimal and adds no visual elements to the page
- It tracks page views automatically without additional configuration
- Analytics requests will appear as `/_vercel/insights/*` routes after deployment
- The implementation is framework-specific for Next.js App Router as documented
